How to navigate the minefield of good and bad taste.
At a recent Table Topics session, our Topicsmaster quoted a news clipping about someone who grafted an ear to his forehead in the name of art. A member responded: &ldquo;We were asked if an ear grafted to the forehead was art. Technically, it&rsquo;s called Forehead Art&hellip;or F-ART. Which gives you my answer to whether or not it&rsquo;s art.&rdquo;
Oops. That joke crossed the invisible line separating appropriate humor from the inappropriate.

